<p id="Par31" class="p">Most emission types are calculated as the product of emission factors per activity level (determined as a function of yields and other characteristics) and activity levels. For some of them, mitigation measures may reduce emissions according to a factor 
 <italic class="italic">mfac</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">a,e</italic>
 </sub> below the standard, uncontrolled amount (=100%). The most important example is the reduction in CH
 <sub class="sub">4</sub> emissions from manure management according to the GAINS (
 <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR16" class="xref">2013</xref>) mitigation options farm scale and community scale anaerobic digestion plants. Formally, 
